There are Events.
The event can be raised by anyone.
There are Event handlers.
Each event can have 0+ handlers by the time of the fire.
Every event handler has it's own order.
Once the event fired, all the event handlers are executed with respect to their order.

There are Requests.
Every Request has it's respected Response.
Response and response handler work the same as event and event handler respectfully.
There are Response Handlers.
They work the same as Event handlers.
There are Response Providers.
They should always provide the Response as the answer on the Request.
Every Request should have 0+ handlers and 1 request provider at the time of fire.
Every Response can have 0+ handlers at the time of fire.